1. Building the image :
	docker build -t nodejs-hello-world:1.0.0 .
Verify whether the image is created 
	docker images

2. Exposing the image in container with port 80 
	docker run -d --name nodejs-hello -p 80:3000 nodejs-hello-world:1.0.0...
	#app port: cont port , so host is available on port 80
Verify it :
	docker ps
	
3. Check whether connection is established via docker hub and also in cli 
	curl http://localhost
	
4. Reterieve the logs 
	docker logs nodejs-hello
	
5. Save the container image to the file 
	docker save nodejs-hello-world:1.0.0 -o nodejs-hello-world-1.0.0.tar
